%h1 A Bugs Life

%p.intro
  New Zealand teems with an estimated 20,000 different insect species. The country’s isolation and temperate climate have given rise to a distinctive insect fauna. More than 90% of species can be found nowhere else, and many have evolved remarkably differently from their relatives overseas

%h2
